## Mode 2: Hybrid CPU+GPU

### Concept

The **GPUMemoryManager** decides which models fit on GPU (by priority and memory budget). High-priority/large models go to GPU with CUDA streams. Remaining models go to CPU with a ThreadPoolExecutor. Both execute **simultaneously**.

### How It Works

```
Step 1: GPUMemoryManager.plan_placement()
         ├─ Sort models by priority (YOLO > ResNet > Signal models)
         ├─ Place models on GPU until VRAM budget is full
         └─ Remaining → CPU

Step 2: Split models into two groups:
         GPU group: [yolov8_small, yolov8_nano, resnet18, ...]
         CPU group: [signal_denoiser, anomaly_detector, ...]

Step 3: For each data batch (simultaneously):
         GPU group → CUDAStreamsEngine (parallel via streams)
         CPU group → ThreadPoolExecutor (parallel via threads)

Step 4: Wait for both groups → merge outputs
```

### When GPU Has Enough VRAM (T4 16GB — Our Case)

All 10 models fit on GPU (1.97 GB total), so `cpu_models = []` and it behaves like single_gpu mode but with smaller batch sizes for memory safety.

### When GPU Has Limited VRAM (e.g., GTX 1650 4GB)

```
GPU (4GB budget): yolov8_small(400MB), resnet18(300MB), yolov8_nano(200MB), efficientnet_b0(200MB)
                  Total: 1100MB ← fits in 4GB with room for batches
CPU (overflow):   signal_denoiser, anomaly_detector, ew_classifier, etc.
                  Run on ThreadPoolExecutor (4 threads)
```

### Visual

```
Timeline (one batch, memory-constrained GPU):

GPU Streams:  ████████░░░░ (YOLO-S)   ← High priority, benefits from GPU
              ░██████░░░░░ (ResNet-18)
              ░░████░░░░░░ (YOLO-N)

CPU Threads:  ███░░░░░░░░░ (EW Classifier)    ← Small, fast on CPU anyway
              ██░░░░░░░░░░ (Signal Denoiser)
              ██░░░░░░░░░░ (Anomaly Detector)

Both groups run SIMULTANEOUSLY
Total time = max(GPU group time, CPU group time)
```

### Code Path

```
benchmark/run_benchmark.py
  → inference/hybrid_cpu_gpu.py::run_hybrid_inference()
    → GPUMemoryManager.plan_placement(model_sizes, priorities)
    → CUDAStreamsEngine(gpu_models_only)
    → ThreadPoolExecutor(cpu_models_only)
    → Run both concurrently per batch
```

### Limitations

- Still limited to one machine
- CPU models are slower than GPU models
- Best when GPU VRAM < total model memory

