## Mode 4: Spark Distributed (GPU)

### Concept

Same as Mode 3, except each partition runs inference on **GPU** instead of CPU. Enabled by setting `SPARK_EXECUTOR_GPU=1`. On a real cluster, each executor is a separate OS process with its own CUDA context — safe to use GPU. With **NVIDIA MPS** enabled, multiple processes share the GPU truly in parallel.

### How It Works

```
Same as Mode 3, except:
  Step 8: Deserialize all 10 models onto CUDA (not CPU)
  Step 9: Run batched inference on GPU

The key difference in the code:
  if torch.cuda.is_available() and os.environ.get("SPARK_EXECUTOR_GPU") == "1":
      device = "cuda"    ← GPU path
  else:
      device = "cpu"     ← CPU path (safe default)
```

### When It's Safe

| Deployment | Safe to use GPU? | Why |
|---|---|---|
| local[*] (threads, 1 process) | Risky (2 partitions max) | Threads share CUDA context |
| Cluster (separate processes) | Yes | Each process has own CUDA context |
| Cluster + MPS | Best | MPS enables true parallel GPU access |

