## Comparison Summary

| Aspect | Single GPU | Hybrid | Spark CPU | Spark GPU |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Throughput (1 node) | 41,908/sec | 32,773/sec | 2,967/sec | 5,329/sec |
| Parallelism method | CUDA Streams | Streams + Threads | Spark partitions | Spark + CUDA |
| GPU utilization | Maximum | Maximum (if fits) | None | Per-partition |
| Scales to N nodes | No | No | Yes (linear) | Yes (linear) |
| Fault tolerance | None | None | Spark retries | Spark retries |
| Memory requirement | All models fit in 1 GPU | Flexible (GPU+CPU split) | CPU RAM only | GPU per node |
| Code file | `single_gpu.py` | `hybrid_cpu_gpu.py` | `distributed_gpu.py` | `distributed_gpu.py` |
| Best for | Edge/workstation | Limited VRAM | CPU-only clusters | GPU clusters |

